channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Biden NATO Summit Confusion Includes Bizarre Gestures—and Even a Struggle With a Chair
White House 'cheap fake' narrative crumbles after Clooney exposes Biden's condition at Hollywood fundraiser
item.description: The Democratic narrative that concerns about Biden's age were unfounded took a hit this week after calls came from Hollywood for the president to drop out.

item.title: Top N.Y. Court Allows 'Equal Rights' Amendment to Appear on November Ballot
item.description: A proposed amendment to New York's constitution to bar discrimination over "gender identity" and "pregnancy outcomes" will appear on the ballot this November, the state's high court ruled Thursday.The decision from the Court of Appeals affirms a lower court ruling from...

item.title: Giorgia Meloni Becomes All of Us While Waiting for a Perpetually Late Joe Biden
Another House Dem calls for Biden to step down after debate performance: ‘Time to pass the torch’
item.description: Rep. Brad Schneider, D-Il., added his name to the growing list of Democrats calling for President Biden to step aside from the presidential race.

item.title: Monmouth Poll: Denying Election Results Problematic
item.description: A Monmouth University poll released Thursday revealed that a majority of U.S. adults consider the refusal to accept election outcomes to be a major problem, The Hill reported.

item.title: Debunking the Remaining Myth: Biden Has Never Been a 'Decent Man'
Biden camp addresses rumors advisers are hatching plan to push president aside
item.description: The White House and Biden campaign denied reports Thursday that advisers are working on a plan to convince the president to bow out of the 2024 election.

item.title: Jason Miller to Newsmax: Trump Ready for All Options
item.description: Former President Donald Trump is ready "for all options" should President Joe Biden withdraw as the Democratic nominee, said Trump campaign senior adviser Jason Miller.

item.title: Eye-Opening Voter Registration Numbers in June Should Raise More Concerns for Dems
Biden’s staunchest supporters featured prominently among potential successors
item.description: While many Democrats call on President Biden to drop out of the race, some of those floated as potential replacements for the nomination remain supportive of his re-election bid.

item.title: Presentation at Army Base Labels Pro-life Group Terrorists
item.description: Anti-abortion organizations were labelled as "terrorist groups" during a training seminar at Fort Liberty in North Carolina, according to images leaked from the base and verified by the Washington Examiner.

item.title: NBC News and Lester Holt to Help the Biden Rehab Effort and the Timing Shows More Media Collusion
Stacey Abrams rejects Biden concerns, says no Joe voters will flip to ‘bombastic, fascistic liar’ Trump
item.description: Former Georgia State House Minority Leader Stacey Abrams voiced her full support for President Biden in an entry in the Atlanta Journal-Constitution

item.title: NY Times: Top Biden Aides 'Convinced' He Must Step Aside
item.description: Longtime aides to President Joe Biden are convinced he will have to drop out of his reelection campaign and are working on ways to get him to leave the race, three sources told The New York Times.
